        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The integration time on source per pointing is 2 min. For a 50 pointing mosaic, this sums up to a total time of 100 min on source. Thus, with the capabilities of ALMA, it will be possible to obtain this unique and highly resolved data set with very good sensitivity of 0.015 Jy for single channel of the spectral line in a short integration time, while it will be 0.4 mJy in our aggregate Bandwidth.

The observations will be performed using band 7. The spectral setup consists of two windows. The CO, HC3N and SiO are set in lower sideband, at 345.796 GHz, 345.609 GHz, and 347.331 GHz, and then HCO+ will fall into upper sideband at 356.734 GHz. Each sideband have a bandwidth of 1875 MHz and gives a velocity resolution of 0.8 km/s. The typical linewidth is about 50 km/s. The coverage between the transitions of choice will be used
for the determination of the continuum. Choosing the medium bandwidth is thus a compromise to achieve
good continuum sensitivity while keeping the problem of line smearing at bay.

To cover the whole GC3-C1 cloud, we need a 90"x90" field (See Fig. 1). This results in 50 beam mosaic (Nyquist sampled). The angular isze of  GC3-C1 is greater than 20". Thus we are requesting supplemental observations with ACA.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
