    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose to carry out higher spatial resolution observations of  HCO+, CO, SiO, HC3N and CH3OH lines as well as continuum at 345 GHz towards the Galactic cloud, GC3-C1 with ALMA. The observations are to  determine the fragmentation, and trace the kinematical structure of GC3-C1. With ALMA  12m configuration complementary with ACA array, we expect that the ALMA can resolve the GC3-C1 into individual components by the continuum image. We also expect to sample the entire cloud envelope using the lower energy HCO+ and CO transitions and resolve the inner hot gas components by use of higher energy HC3N and CH3OH lines. The correlator setup will include SiO, an excellent tracer of hot shock gas in filaments and outflows, using for observing the kinematics. The higher spatial resolution observations will mass distribution of the cluster, velocity field information and gas flow of different cluster member, which will be crucial to understanding masssive star formation in the Galactic center, further understanding the forming mode of young steller cluster. </prp:abstract>
